  "texts": [
    "Assume that at inference time we face a classification problem with c classes, where c ⊂ C. We extract features from each training sample with a pre-trained Perceiver Resampler and fit a classifier (either a linear layer or a full-sized model) that predicts these c classes.",
    "With this approach, we reduced the 167-class classification problem to a more tractable subset of classes.",
    "For BCC vs. ¬BCC, we considered all samples that are not BCC to be ¬BCC and fitted an MLP with 100 neurons.",
    "For Melanoma vs. ¬Melanoma, we followed the same procedure.",
    "For all other classification tasks, we only trained on the specific subset."
  ],
